ok so last night was first trip i have taken yet that was over a 15 minute ride.. went across town and took me about 30 minutes... the temp was about high 70 low 8o's...thats usually when temp gets right up there..(it didnt though)
  i am still not sure if i did anything to help but so far so good...
   
   
  yes i was speaking of both sides of the heater box i plugged off and already had the side that goes into engine bay blocked all along so that wasnt a concern but i think redoing the battery tray made a world of difference..
  the air flow can flow through there like its suppose to..
   
  the condensor needs to be replaced but i dont know what condensor to buy...
  also now got to get another new set of points...
  that will make a difference as well... i have a condensor here but cant match numbers on busdepot site... anyone got a list of condensor numbers so i can match this one up i got to see if i can use it... ???
   
  will have to pull dizzy later on to see about what the dizzy numbers are and maybe match them that aways....
   
  thanks for al the help will keep updated.. also thinking of installing my external oil cooler i got....
  that will or should help tremendously...
   
  also i did vaccum out in the tiin holes and changed spark plugs .. the ones that came out #3 and #4 were soot black and numbers #1 and #2 were light ash grey .. so that means then that 3 and 4 are burning rich and 1 and 2 are burning lean..??
   
  so my carb might honestly be a big problem here also...as i have also thought all along...?
