Darren Evans-Young <darren(-at-)bama.ua.edu> wrote:
  On Mon, 22 May 2006, Chai wrote:

>i also found my battery tray is gone gone gone... so i cut some sheet
>metal and was able to bond the sheet metal in there and seal it up pretty
>good with roof cement (roof patch)
>

...

> i also plugged off my holes for my heater boxes...
>

Right there are two places where hot engine heat can get
sucked back into the cooling fan.

I assume the holes for the heater boxes are the ones
in the engine compartment. Yes, plug those if you
don't have a fan (w/flaps) and a hose leading from the
holes to the fan.

I cut an aluminun soft drink can in half and crammed it on
there temporarily.

